    <h1>Roofing Cost Estimator: How to Price Commercial Roofing Jobs</h1>
    <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:#64748b;margin-bottom:2rem">Published June 16, 2026</p>

    <p>Commercial roofing estimating requires precision. Unlike residential projects, commercial roofs involve larger surface areas, specialized materials, complex flashing details, and strict building code requirements. A single estimating error on a commercial project can cost thousands in lost profit.</p>

    <p>This guide walks you through the complete process of estimating commercial roofing costs using TradeQuote Pro's built-in <a href="/tradequote/">roofing cost estimator</a>.</p>

    <h2>Understanding Commercial Roofing Systems</h2>
    <p>Before you can estimate costs, you need to understand the roofing system being specified. Common commercial roofing systems include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>TPO (Thermoplastic Polyolefin)</strong> — $5.50-$9.50 per sq ft. Most popular for low-slope commercial roofs.</li>
      <li><strong>EPDM (Ethylene Propylene Diene Monomer)</strong> — $4.50-$8.50 per sq ft. Durable rubber roofing.</li>
      <li><strong>PVC (Polyvinyl Chloride)</strong> — $6.00-$10.50 per sq ft. Excellent chemical resistance.</li>
      <li><strong>Modified Bitumen</strong> — $4.00-$7.50 per sq ft. Traditional built-up roofing.</li>
      <li><strong>Metal Roofing</strong> — $8.00-$14.00 per sq ft. Premium, long-lasting option.</li>
      <li><strong>Built-Up Roofing (BUR)</strong> — $3.50-$7.00 per sq ft. Multi-ply asphalt system.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How to Calculate Roofing Material Quantities</h2>
    <p>Accurate material takeoffs are the foundation of a reliable estimate. For commercial roofing, you need to calculate:</p>

    <h3>Roof Surface Area</h3>
    <p>Measure the roof's length and width at the exterior walls. For simple rectangular roofs, multiply length × width. For complex roofs with multiple sections, calculate each section separately and add them together. Don't forget to account for roof pitch — a 4:12 pitch adds approximately 5% to the surface area compared to a flat roof measurement.</p>

    <h3>Waste and Overlap Factors</h3>
    <p>Add waste factors based on roof complexity: 5-10% for simple rectangular roofs, 10-15% for roofs with penetrations and curbs, and 15-20% for roofs with multiple angles and flashings.</p>

    <h3>Additional Material Quantities</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Insulation</strong> — Calculate based on R-value requirements</li>
      <li><strong>Fasteners</strong> — Approximately 25-30 per square (100 sq ft) for membrane attachment</li>
      <li><strong>Flashing</strong> — Linear feet of perimeter plus penetrations</li>
      <li><strong>Sealant</strong> — One tube per 20-25 linear feet of flashing</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Labor Cost Estimation for Commercial Roofing</h2>
    <p>Labor costs for commercial roofing vary by region and crew size. Average production rates:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>TPO/PVC membrane installation</strong> — 15-25 squares per crew per day</li>
      <li><strong>EPDM installation</strong> — 20-30 squares per crew per day</li>
      <li><strong>Modified bitumen</strong> — 15-20 squares per crew per day</li>
      <li><strong>Metal roofing</strong> — 10-18 squares per crew per day</li>
    </ul>
    <p>A standard commercial roofing crew consists of 4-6 workers with a foreman. Hourly rates including burden range from $25-$45 per hour depending on your market.</p>

